<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01 · Cleveland Range steamers in SoCal</p>
    <h2>SteamCraft is the convection steamer specialty.</h2>

    <p>Cleveland Range's SteamCraft convection steamer line is a core product of the brand alongside the steam-jacketed kettle line (covered separately on the kettle-repair side). SteamCraft steamers cook food via low-pressure steam in a convection-circulating chamber, which preserves food texture and color better than high-pressure pressure-cookers and faster than open-pot boiling. Common applications: vegetable cooking in cafeteria service, seafood cooking in restaurant kitchens, rice and grain cooking in institutional volumes, dim sum and dumpling cooking in Asian-cuisine kitchens.</p>

    <p>Across SoCal, Cleveland Range SteamCraft units appear in: institutional kitchens (LAUSD, UC and CSU dining services, hospital cafeterias), large catering operations, banquet kitchens, and restaurant kitchens with significant steam-cooked menu items. SteamChef 24CGA gas-fired countertop is common in smaller kitchens; SteamPro freestanding double-compartment units are common in high-volume institutional installations. Welbilt acquired Cleveland Range in 2008; Ali Group acquired Welbilt in 2022. Convotherm combi ovens (sister Welbilt brand) are often paired with Cleveland Range steamers in larger installations.</p>

    <p>$120 commercial diagnostic, applied to repair. Same-day response across LA, OC, Ventura. Phones answered 24/7. Parent: <a href="/commercial/steamer-repair/">commercial steamer repair</a>. Sister brand: <a href="/commercial/kettle-repair/brands/cleveland-range/">Cleveland Range kettles</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">02 · Cleveland Range steamer product lines</p>
    <h2>Series and common service items.</h2>

    <h3 class="brand-h3">SteamChef 24CGA, Gas-Fired Countertop</h3>
    <p>Compact gas-fired countertop convection steamer. Self-contained boiler heats water to generate steam; convection fan circulates steam through the cooking chamber. Common service items: gas valve, thermopile (year 4-7), water inlet valve (year 5-8), water-level probe (LA hard water-driven, scale buildup year 2-4), heating element (gas burner element on the boiler heat exchanger, year 6-9), door gasket (year 4-7), drain valve.</p>

    <h3 class="brand-h3">SteamChef Electric Countertop and SteamPro Freestanding</h3>
    <p>Electric-heated boiler variants. SteamPro is the larger freestanding configuration in single and double-compartment versions. Common service items: heating element ($640-920), water inlet valve, water-level probes (LA hard water scale management is critical here), door gasket, contactor relay, control board on digital units.</p>

    <h3 class="brand-h3">Boilerless Steamers</h3>
    <p>Newer Cleveland Range product line that generates cooking steam by spraying water onto a hot heating element rather than maintaining a continuous steam generator. Advantages: no continuous boiler scale management, smaller footprint, faster startup. Service items different from boiler-equipped: water spray system, heating element exposure, vapor management. Failure modes are different and less frequent than boiler-equipped, but specialty parts may have longer lead times.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">03 · Real Cleveland Range steamer repairs</p>
    <h2>Composite stories from the route.</h2>
    <div class="story-grid">
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>LAUSD elementary school cafeteria, SteamPro double-compartment electric (year 7)</h3>
        <p>Steam output dropping over 3 weeks before customer call. Diagnosed: heavy scale buildup in steam generator (LA hard water, no water softener at inlet). Performed full descale + water-level probe service, recommended water softener install. Set facility on quarterly descale PM. Total: $120 plus $360 descale plus 120 minutes labor = $660. Plus separate water softener install scope referred to plumbing partner.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>UCLA campus dining, SteamChef 24CGA gas (year 6)</h3>
        <p>Pilot wouldn't stay lit. Diagnosed thermopile failure: 175 mV (needs 250+). Replaced thermopile. Tested pilot through full burner cycle. Total: $120 plus $360 part plus 75 minutes labor = $580.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Cedars-Sinai hospital cafeteria, SteamPro electric (year 9)</h3>
        <p>Heating element open circuit. Replaced element with OEM Cleveland Range part. While there, performed descale on the steam generator (overdue per the operator's schedule). HACCP temperature documentation provided. Total: $120 plus $720 element plus $260 descale plus 150 minutes labor = $1,250.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Marina del Rey hotel banquet, boilerless steamer (year 5)</h3>
        <p>Steam output reduced. Boilerless architecture so no scale issue; diagnosed water spray nozzle clogged from grease film + minor mineral. Cleaned spray nozzle, tested steam output recovery. Total: $120 plus 60 minutes labor = $200.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

